"title": "6687: mercy, nature of God's",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6687",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A central aspect of God's character,  expressed in his covenant relationships  with undeserving people.</p>\n<h2>God is merciful</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:9\">DAN 9:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4\">EPH 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:14\">2SA 24:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:31\">NEH 9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:7\">PSA 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:6\">PSA 25:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:12\">JER 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:78\">LUK 1:78</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:2\">1TI 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:11\">JAS 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:3\">1PE 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:3\">2JN 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:2\">JUD 1:2</a></p>\n<h2>God's mercy is expressed in his faithfulness to his covenant with his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:18-Mic7:20\">MIC 7:18–7:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:31\">DEU 4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:9\">DEU 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:23-1Kgs8:24\">1KI 8:23–8:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:5\">NEH 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:30-Neh9:31\">NEH 9:30–9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:1\">PSA 143:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:9\">ISA 63:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:54-Luke1:55\">LUK 1:54–1:55</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:69-Luke1:75\">LUK 1:69–1:75</a></p>\n<h2>God's faithfulness and mercy are never-ending</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:17\">PSA 103:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:6\">PSA 25:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:1\">PSA 106:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:132\">PSA 119:132</a></p>\n<h2>God's mercy and grace are seen in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:22-Rom3:24\">ROM 3:22–3:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:15\">ROM 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:21\">JUD 1:21</a></p>\n<h2>God's mercy is not confined to the Jewish nation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:29-Rom3:30\">ROM 3:29–3:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:6\">ISA 49:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:2\">JON 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:12\">ROM 10:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:28-Rom11:32\">ROM 11:28–11:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:8-Rom15:12\">ROM 15:8–15:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:14\">GAL 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:6-Eph3:8\">EPH 3:6–3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:27\">COL 1:27</a></p>\n<h2>God chooses when and where to exercise his mercy</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:15-Rom9:16\">ROM 9:15–9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:19\">EXO 33:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:7-Deut7:8\">DEU 7:7–7:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:12\">PSA 33:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:16\">JHN 15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:27-1Cor1:29\">1CO 1:27–1:29</a></p>\n<h2>God's responds in mercy to those who call to him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:9\">PSA 6:9</a></strong> <em>There are many appeals to God's mercy in the book of Psalms.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:28\">1KI 8:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:19\">2CH 6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:15\">JOB 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:18\">DAN 9:18</a></p>",
